  "candidate_text": "Kai runs the faucet without filling anything, his back still to the letter, mouthing 'I know I made it harder'\u2014then stopping because the word 'harder' sounds like a negotiation, like he's already bargaining down from something worse. The harbor is in the room with him: the specific quality of her silence after she said what she said, the way it wasn't an ending so much as a door left open at a temperature he couldn't stand. He tries the sentence a third time, dropping 'I know' entirely, starting instead with 'The silence wasn't\u2014' and his jaw closes on the rest because he can hear her finish it for him, accurately, in a voice that has never once needed to be cruel to land.",
